:: Act 0 Entry [Act0 Entry]
**ACT 0 — First Blood (Prologue)**

A village burns. Bandits run. Something older watches.

[[Approach the village gates->Ashford Gates]]

:: Ashford Gates [Act0 Dialogue]
The **gates of Ashford** stand half-open. A guard, soot on his brow, blocks your path.

''Guard:'' “Hold. State your profession, traveller. If you’ve come to gawk at our misery—keep walking.”

Choose your class:
* [[“Fighter. I know my way around steel.”->Choose Fighter]]
* [[“Rogue. I go where others can’t.”->Choose Rogue]]
* [[“Wizard. I study forces most fear.”->Choose Wizard]]
* [[“Cleric. I mend what darkness breaks.”->Choose Cleric]]

You can also question the guard:
* [[“What happened here?”->Guard Report]]
* [[“Which way did they go?”->Guard Report]]

:: Choose Fighter [Act0 Dialogue]
<<set $class to "Fighter">>
The guard eyes your arms, your stance.
''Guard:'' “Good. We need folk who don’t flinch.”
[[Continue->Guard Report]]

:: Choose Rogue [Act0 Dialogue]
<<set $class to "Rogue">>
The guard’s gaze flicks to your hands.
''Guard:'' “Quiet feet might catch loud thieves.”
[[Continue->Guard Report]]

:: Choose Wizard [Act0 Dialogue]
<<set $class to "Wizard">>
The guard swallows, uneasy.
''Guard:'' “If you can turn flame aside… we’ll not refuse you.”
[[Continue->Guard Report]]

:: Choose Cleric [Act0 Dialogue]
<<set $class to "Cleric">>
The guard exhales, relief and doubt.
''Guard:'' “Then you’ll find no shortage of wounds.”
[[Continue->Guard Report]]

:: Guard Report [Act0 Dialogue]
''Guard:'' “Bandits came in the night. Took anything of value and set fire to half the village.”

Ask:
* [[“How many were there?”->Guard Questions]]
* [[“Anyone hurt?”->Guard Questions]]
* [[“Which way did they go?”->Guard Questions]]
* [[[Intimidate] “Tell me everything. Now.”->Intimidate Guard]]

[[Enter the burning streets->Burning Village]]

:: Guard Questions [Act0 Dialogue]
<<set $injuryInfo to true>>
''Guard:'' “Four… maybe five. Fast. Organised. They fled **east**, into **Blackwood Forest**.”
[[Back->Guard Report]]

:: Intimidate Guard [Act0 Dialogue]
<<set $tracksFound to true>>
You step close. Your voice leaves no room for evasion.

''Guard:'' “All right! East—by the old cart road. Look for wheel ruts and broken branches. Their leader has a **scarred face**… cruel laugh.”
[[Enter the burning streets->Burning Village]]

:: Burning Village [Act0 Exploration]
Ashford is chaos—smouldering beams, frantic shouts, the stink of wet ash.

You can help (and learn):
* [[Speak to the Innkeeper->Innkeeper]]
* [[Speak to the Blacksmith->Blacksmith]]
* [[Speak to a Wounded Militia member->Militia]]
* [[Find the Mayor->Mayor]]

Or leave at once:
* [[Follow the trail into Blackwood->Forest Entrance]]

:: Innkeeper [Act0 Dialogue]
An innkeeper stands amid cinders, clutching a scorched lockbox.

''Innkeeper:'' “My life savings—gone. Their leader… a scarred face, and that laugh—like a knife.”

* [[“What did they take?”->Innkeeper More]]
* [[“Did they mention anything?”->Innkeeper More]]
[[Back to the streets->Burning Village]]

:: Innkeeper More [Act0 Dialogue]
''Innkeeper:'' “Gold, trinkets… but they seemed to hunt for something specific. Like they had a list.”
[[Back->Innkeeper]]

:: Blacksmith [Act0 Dialogue]
The forge is ransacked. The blacksmith wipes soot from his eyes.

''Blacksmith:'' “If you truly mean to hunt them—take this. Better it bites bandit flesh than rusts in ash.”

<<if $hasWeapon is false>>
* [[Accept the basic weapon->Take Weapon]]
<</if>>
* [[Decline politely->Decline Weapon]]

[[Back to the streets->Burning Village]]

:: Take Weapon [Act0 Exploration]
<<set $hasWeapon to true>>
You take a serviceable blade—nick-marked, but balanced.

''Blacksmith:'' “Bring back what you can. Or at least bring back justice.”
[[Back->Blacksmith]]

:: Decline Weapon [Act0 Dialogue]
''Blacksmith:'' “Hmph. Then may your courage be sharper than steel.”
[[Back->Blacksmith]]

:: Militia [Act0 Dialogue]
A wounded militia scout grips your sleeve.

''Militia:'' “They fled east. Four—five at most. Not just rabble… they moved like soldiers.”

* [[“Any sign of where they’re headed?”->Militia More]]
[[Back->Burning Village]]

:: Militia More [Act0 Dialogue]
''Militia:'' “Deeper in Blackwood. There’s an old trail where carts used to run.”
[[Back->Militia]]

:: Mayor [Act0 Dialogue]
The mayor stands before a half-burned hall, jaw clenched.

''Mayor:'' “Recover what they stole. Bring them to justice. Ashford will pay what little it can.”

* [[Accept the quest->Accept Quest]]
* [[Decline and leave (end prologue)->Decline Quest]]

:: Accept Quest [Act0 Outcome]
''Mayor:'' “Then you have Ashford’s gratitude… and what coin we can scrape together.”
[[Into the forest->Forest Entrance]]

:: Decline Quest [Act0 Outcome]
You turn away from the smoke and the pleading eyes.
**END (Prologue declined)**

